description: The antigenic switching rate per infected red blood cell per asexual cycle. See Parasite_Switch_Type for different switching patterns.
Fraction of gametocytes that are male.
Average fraction of gametocytes in a blood meal that are successful in infecting the mosquito in the absence of other modulating effects, such as fever.
The fraction of infected red blood cells producing gametocytes
The number of distinct merozoite surface protein variants for P. falciparum malaria in the overall parasite population in the simulation, not necessarily in an individual
The number of distinct non-specific types of P. falciparum malaria
The number of distince Plasmodium falciparum erythrocyte membrane protein 1 (PfEMP1) variants for P falciparum malaria in the overall parasite population in the simulation

parameter_label: Max Fever Kill Rate of iRBCs
description: The maximum kill rate for infected red blood cells due to the inflammatory innate immune response. As fever increases above 38.5 degrees Celsius, the kill rate becomes succesively higher along a sigmoidal curve approaching this maximal rate
The rate of gametocyte survival from one development stage to the next in the absence of drugs or inflammatory response
The fraction of merozoites inhibited from invading new erythrocytes when MSP1-specific antibody level is 1
The factor that adjusts Antibody_Capacity_Growth_Rate for less immunogenic surface proteins called minor epitopes
The nonspecific antigenicity factor that adjusts antibody iRBC kill rate to account for iRBCs caused by antibody responses to antigenically weak surface proteins
The level of bloodstream infection, measured in iRBC per microliter, at which stimulation of the innate inflammatory immune respnose is half its maximum value
The strength of inflammatory response inactivation of gametocytes
